<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
China, Thailand, Korea (Chen et al. 2014). Recorded from Thailand by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carmean, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="35 - 76" title="Phylogenetic revision of the parasitoid wasp family Trigonalidae (Hymenoptera)." url="10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" volume="23" year="1998">Carmean and Kimsey (1998)</bibRefCitation>
and Chen et al. (2014), but no localities given. Chen et al. (2013) recorded 11 provinces in China but not Sichuan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">The largely reddish-brown color and lack of a medio-apical process on the second metasomal sternite will help separate this species. We examined only one specimen from Thailand, but the species seems widespread in Asia.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
